Toronto Blue Jays' catcher Russell Martin, left, attempts to tag Texas Rangers' Rougned Odor, right, who scores during the 14th inning of baseball Game 2 of the American League Division Series in Toronto, Friday, Oct. 9, 2015. TORONTO (AP) â€” Backup infielder Hanser Alberto singled home the go-ahead run in the 14th inning and the Texas Rangers beat the Toronto Blue Jays 6-4 Friday for a 2-0 lead in the best-of-five American League Division Series.
